  "prompt": "What do we call Buffalo meat? Is it bacon?",
  "response": "No, buffalo meat is not bacon. Buffalo meat is typically called \"buffalo meat\" or \"buffalo beef.\" When it comes from a specific type of buffalo (water buffalo), it might be referred to as \"water buffalo meat.\" In some contexts, particularly when referring to the American bison (which is often incorrectly called a buffalo), the meat might be called \"bison meat\" or simply \"bison.\"\n\nBacon specifically refers to cured and sliced meat from a pig's belly or back.",
